One person was shot dead and five others were wounded when three armed men opened fire at a tavern in Ficksburg in the Free State on Friday night. Police spokesperson Captain Phumelelo Dhlamini said it was alleged that three armed men arrived at the tavern in Meqheleng at around 21:00 and shot dead one person at the gate. Dhlamini said the gunmen then walked inside the tavern and opened fire, wounding five people. The victims were rushed to hospital. No arrests were made. Anyone with information can contact detective Lieutenant-Colonel Kgolanyane at 082 3019 578 or call our Crime Stop number at 08600 10111.